# Project Rules for Cursor

## Available Commands

Use these commands in chat to invoke workflows:

### Workflow Commands

#### /sk-team-feature
Start full feature development with multi-agent team.
Phases: Discovery → Planning → Testing → Implementation → Review → Acceptance

#### /sk-team-quick
Quick fix workflow for bugfixes, typos, and small changes.
Phases: Developer → Code Review

#### /sk-team-status
Show status of active team workflows.

#### /sk-team-help
Show documentation for multi-agent team workflow.

### Onboarding Commands

#### /sk-onboard
Full project onboarding - discover structure + generate navigation rules.

#### /sk-discover-project
Discover project structure, tech stack, domains, and API surface.

#### /sk-explore-codebase
Explore codebase and generate check-before-create navigation rules.

### Utility Commands

#### /sk-code-review
Review uncommitted changes with fresh context.
Focuses on patterns linters miss.

#### /sk-explore-codestyle
Analyze project and generate code style guidelines.
Detects stack, extracts linter rules, identifies patterns.

### Context Commands

#### /sk-copy-context
Copy current session context to clipboard for handoff.

## Agent Roles

When working on features, these agents handle different phases:

- **sk-product-analyst** - Requirements gathering (WHAT & WHY)
- **sk-architect** - System design (HOW)
- **sk-tester** - TDD red phase (failing tests)
- **sk-developer** - TDD green phase (implementation)
- **sk-code-reviewer** - Code quality review
- **sk-acceptance-reviewer** - Business validation

## Artifacts Location

All feature artifacts are stored in:
```
openspec/changes/<feature-name>/
├── proposal.md      # Requirements
├── design.md        # Technical design
├── tasks.md         # Task breakdown
└── VERIFICATION.md  # Acceptance result
```
